  "body": "Prior us moving to `status.prod` and Waku2, when a user joined a community, the user's node would request/receive history messages from mailservers.\r\n\r\nThis is important because otherwise the user will join an empty chat room and only sees new messages that come in in real-time.\r\n\r\nThis is also important for the community protocol to work properly, as the member node needs to receive the latest published magnet link message to get access to possibly existing community archives.\r\n\r\nFor some reason, I don't see the member node receiving history messages from store nodes upon joining a community anymore.\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce:\r\n\r\n1. Run two instances of Status Desktop both with a different account, owner and member\r\n2. Create a community with the owner account, make sure to also send a few messages in the #general channel \r\n3. Invite/share community with the member account\r\n4. Member account goes to community and requests access\r\n5. Owner accepts\r\n6. Once member node receives ACK from owner, it sees all channels/categories\r\n\r\nAfter 6, history message should be fetched from store nodes (from past 30 days), but this doesn't seem to be happening.\r\n\r\n/cc'ing @richard-ramos ",
