    "body": "Okay, quick update here.\r\n\r\nWhat we're experiencing here is the result of how we changed the way users will enter communities.\r\n\r\nIn the past, users would receive some sort of community share link, they would request access from the chat view (at this point, the member account hasn't subscribed to the community channel yet) and as soon as the request was accepted, the community would be added to the app, the node would subscribe to the community channel and also request historic messages (past 30 days).\r\n\r\nNow, this is a bit different:\r\n\r\nThe member account receives a share link, but instead of requesting access here, the account uses that link to \"visit\" the community. By doing that, it also subscribes to the community channel to receive the community description. It will also receive anything else that was published on that channel (including magnet link messages for the archive protocol).\r\n**Now** the user requests access and has already seen the latest community channel messages. So after the request to join has been accepted, it looks like historic messages from the community channel aren't fetched (when in fact they have been fetched already)\r\n\r\nI'll close this issue.\r\n",
